WEBVTT

1
00:00:50.130 --> 00:00:52.590
-Is it a girl?
- Yes.

2
00:00:52.670 --> 00:00:54.380
Show me its arm.

3
00:00:54.469 --> 00:00:57.340
- She bears the mark.
- No!

4
00:01:00.009 --> 00:01:03.520
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

5
00:01:05.939 --> 00:01:08.060
- Help me!
- I can't.

6
00:01:08.150 --> 00:01:10.939
- They're going to kill her.

7
00:01:18.819 --> 00:01:23.370
Oh. thank you. Ethna. Thank you.

8
00:01:31.879 --> 00:01:34.459
Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!

9
00:01:58.819 --> 00:02:01.319
You cannot
stop the prophecy!

10
00:02:01.409 --> 00:02:04.329
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

11
00:02:04.409 --> 00:02:09.250
- No. No!
- Where's the baby?

12
00:02:09.330 --> 00:02:11.750
The midwife.
Find that baby. Sorsha.

13
00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:15.210
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

14
00:02:15.259 --> 00:02:17.379
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

15
00:02:17.469 --> 00:02:19.550
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

16
00:02:19.629 --> 00:02:23.219
- Silence. wench.
- My baby will finish you!
- Kill her.

17
00:05:50.430 --> 00:05:52.430
Dada! Dada!

18
00:05:55.850 --> 00:05:59.149
-Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!

19
00:06:00.399 --> 00:06:03.649
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

20
00:06:03.689 --> 00:06:05.649
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

21
00:06:05.689 --> 00:06:07.990
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

22
00:06:12.990 --> 00:06:15.540
Come on.

23
00:06:17.870 --> 00:06:20.920
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

24
00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:23.920
But. Dada. it's a baby.

25
00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.800
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

26
00:06:28.879 --> 00:06:32.430
- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?

27
00:06:32.509 --> 00:06:34.850
Daikinis are big.

28
00:06:34.889 --> 00:06:38.019
- Giants who live far away.

29
00:06:38.100 --> 00:06:40.399
Oh. she's so cute.

30
00:06:40.480 --> 00:06:44.519
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

31
00:06:44.569 --> 00:06:49.819
We'll push it downstream and forget
we ever saw it. Come on.

32
00:06:49.899 --> 00:06:51.819
- Come on.
- Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

33
00:06:51.870 --> 00:06:56.040
Shhh! It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

34
00:06:56.120 --> 00:06:59.579
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

35
00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:04.959
Mr. Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!

36
00:07:05.050 --> 00:07:07.009
Baaa!

37
00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:13.930
Ufgood. you still haven't
paid your debts to me.

38
00:07:14.009 --> 00:07:16.009
Where did you
get these seeds?

39
00:07:16.100 --> 00:07:18.850
Well. maybe I used magic.

40
00:07:18.930 --> 00:07:22.850
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

41
00:07:22.939 --> 00:07:26.519
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

42
00:07:26.569 --> 00:07:30.029
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

43
00:07:30.110 --> 00:07:33.160
- There's no law against that.

44
00:07:33.240 --> 00:07:38.410
Willow. you didn't leave
them alone by the river?

45
00:07:38.449 --> 00:07:40.790
Magic?
You'll need magic...

46
00:07:40.870 --> 00:07:43.250
if you expect to get your planting
done before the rains start.

47
00:07:45.290 --> 00:07:50.800
I will have this land. And you're
gonna end up working in the mines.

48
00:07:53.009 --> 00:07:56.759
- Baaa-

49
00:07:59.889 --> 00:08:02.889
Oh. you're lovely.

50
00:08:02.939 --> 00:08:04.939
- Yes. you are.

51
00:08:05.019 --> 00:08:09.480
- Kiaya!
- Oh. Willow!

52
00:08:09.529 --> 00:08:14.449
- Good girl. Good girl.
- Under no condition whatsoever...

53
00:08:14.529 --> 00:08:17.279
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

54
00:08:17.329 --> 00:08:22.079
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on. Come on.

55
00:08:22.160 --> 00:08:24.209
There we are. Come on.

56
00:08:24.290 --> 00:08:26.920
Hey. I will not be ignored!

57
00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:30.670
Mims? Ranon?

58
00:08:41.679 --> 00:08:43.809
- You're gonna be all clean.

59
00:08:50.480 --> 00:08:53.779
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

60
00:08:53.860 --> 00:08:56.450
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

61
00:08:56.529 --> 00:08:59.330
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

62
00:08:59.409 --> 00:09:02.330
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?

63
00:09:02.370 --> 00:09:05.419
That's right. He's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!

64
00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:09.539
- Willow. calm down.
- Calm down?

65
00:09:09.629 --> 00:09:11.669
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

66
00:09:11.759 --> 00:09:15.509
Love. the High Aldwin hasn't
picked a new apprentice in years.

67
00:09:15.549 --> 00:09:18.850
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

68
00:09:21.600 --> 00:09:25.269
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

69
00:09:25.350 --> 00:09:28.149
- Hold her while I get some milk.
- Oh. no. no. Oh.

70
00:09:35.779 --> 00:09:39.240
- Dada. she likes you.

71
00:09:46.250 --> 00:09:47.419
- Bye.

72
00:09:47.419 --> 00:09:50.539
- Bye.

73
00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:54.509
- Come on. kids. Let's go.

74
00:10:00.549 --> 00:10:04.139
I will now magic ally join the rings!

75
00:10:26.120 --> 00:10:28.710
- Whoa-ah!

76
00:10:33.500 --> 00:10:35.919
Thank you. son.

77
00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:41.009
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

78
00:10:56.190 --> 00:10:58.450
Give me a ripe one. Good.

79
00:11:04.659 --> 00:11:09.159
- And now. for my final amazing feat.

80
00:11:09.250 --> 00:11:14.090
- I will make this entire pig disappear!

81
00:11:22.139 --> 00:11:27.269
- Mims. see?
- Please. watch very closely.

82
00:11:27.350 --> 00:11:32.980
- Wuppitybairn. deru. deru!

83
00:11:35.230 --> 00:11:37.649
- Well-
- What happened to your pig?

84
00:11:40.360 --> 00:11:43.409
No!
Hey. come here. you!

85
00:11:47.830 --> 00:11:51.250
I had seen enough.

86
00:12:06.350 --> 00:12:09.639
Attention!
The High Aldwin...

87
00:12:09.720 --> 00:12:12.639
-will now make his choice
for his new apprentice!
- You'll be all right.

88
00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:16.149
Bring forth the hopefuls.

89
00:12:16.230 --> 00:12:18.649
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

90
00:12:18.730 --> 00:12:22.490
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

91
00:12:22.570 --> 00:12:25.029
Is this a joke?

92
00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:29.580
- Willow?

93
00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:37.460
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

94
00:12:37.500 --> 00:12:42.090
Forget all you know...
or think you know.

95
00:12:42.169 --> 00:12:46.179
All that your require
is your intuition.

96
00:12:46.259 --> 00:12:50.350
Now. the power
to control the world...

97
00:12:50.429 --> 00:12:54.940
is in which finger?

98
00:13:36.899 --> 00:13:41.440
- No apprentice this year!

99
00:14:01.840 --> 00:14:05.220
- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!

100
00:14:05.299 --> 00:14:08.220
Take Ranon in there. quick!

101
00:14:16.100 --> 00:14:19.059
- Mims!

102
00:14:20.440 --> 00:14:22.570
- Mims!

103
00:14:30.820 --> 00:14:35.659
- Mims!
- Dada-

104
00:14:36.909 --> 00:14:40.000
- I'm scared. Dada!

105
00:14:50.299 --> 00:14:52.889
Come on!

106
00:15:10.529 --> 00:15:13.490
- Vohnkar!

107
00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:25.919
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

108
00:15:28.259 --> 00:15:30.049
Dada! Dada!

109
00:15:33.389 --> 00:15:35.639
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

110
00:15:38.679 --> 00:15:42.480
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

111
00:15:49.860 --> 00:15:53.200
Kiaya!
Kiaya!

112
00:15:53.279 --> 00:15:56.279
- I'm here.

113
00:16:00.370 --> 00:16:04.000
- Oh. Kiaya.

114
00:16:04.080 --> 00:16:06.289
We can't keep
the baby. Kiaya.

115
00:16:06.340 --> 00:16:09.210
We have to take her
to the village council.

116
00:16:22.690 --> 00:16:27.610
Silence! One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

117
00:16:27.690 --> 00:16:30.070
And you can be assured
that they won't give up...

118
00:16:30.149 --> 00:16:32.110
until they find what
they're looking for!

119
00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:35.450
-It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?

120
00:16:35.529 --> 00:16:38.029
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

121
00:16:38.080 --> 00:16:43.210
- In the pit! In the pit!

122
00:16:43.289 --> 00:16:45.419
In the pit! In the pit!

123
00:16:45.500 --> 00:16:48.799
-In the pit! In the pit!
- Willow.

124
00:16:48.879 --> 00:16:53.220
- Willow Ufgood.

125
00:16:53.299 --> 00:16:55.759
Come forward.

126
00:17:01.429 --> 00:17:06.769
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

127
00:17:12.359 --> 00:17:14.529
- A Daikini child.

128
00:17:14.609 --> 00:17:17.819
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

129
00:17:17.910 --> 00:17:18.990
Yeah!

130
00:17:19.079 --> 00:17:22.369
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

131
00:17:22.450 --> 00:17:25.079
This child is special!

132
00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:29.460
This child must be taken beyond
the boundaries of our village.

133
00:17:29.539 --> 00:17:32.589
All the way across
the great river...

134
00:17:32.670 --> 00:17:34.759
to the Daikini crossroads.

135
00:17:34.839 --> 00:17:39.549
- Well. who'll do that?
- It seems only fair...

136
00:17:39.599 --> 00:17:42.970
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

137
00:17:43.059 --> 00:17:46.019
be the very man who
plucked it out of the river.

138
00:17:47.599 --> 00:17:50.230
- I nominate Willow Ufgood.

139
00:17:50.269 --> 00:17:52.819
No!

140
00:17:52.900 --> 00:17:56.450
I will consult the bones!

141
00:18:03.829 --> 00:18:09.329
- The bones tell me... nothing.

142
00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:14.920
Do you have any love
for this child?

143
00:18:23.349 --> 00:18:27.809
Yes. Yes. I do.

144
00:18:27.890 --> 00:18:32.319
- The bones have spoken!

145
00:18:32.359 --> 00:18:36.319
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

146
00:18:36.400 --> 00:18:40.490
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

147
00:18:40.569 --> 00:18:43.079
But you will need help.

148
00:18:43.160 --> 00:18:48.500
Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?

149
00:18:50.539 --> 00:18:54.670
- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.

150
00:18:54.710 --> 00:18:58.009
- Excellent choice.
- I'll go!

151
00:18:58.089 --> 00:19:00.549
Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

152
00:19:00.640 --> 00:19:03.349
No! Not vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

153
00:19:03.390 --> 00:19:06.599
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

154
00:19:14.609 --> 00:19:17.190
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

155
00:19:17.279 --> 00:19:20.660
And according to the bones...

156
00:19:20.740 --> 00:19:24.119
- Bh-
-That leader is...

157
00:19:24.200 --> 00:19:25.619
...you. Burglekutt!

158
00:19:25.619 --> 00:19:26.619
you. Burglekutt!

159
00:19:26.700 --> 00:19:30.170
vohnkar!

160
00:19:30.250 --> 00:19:34.339
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

161
00:19:34.420 --> 00:19:39.720
When I held up my fingers
what was your first impulse?

162
00:19:39.799 --> 00:19:43.720
- Well. it was stupid.
-Just tell me.

163
00:19:43.759 --> 00:19:48.220
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha! That was the correct answer.

164
00:19:48.309 --> 00:19:53.059
You lack faith in yourself.
More than anyone in the village.

165
00:19:53.099 --> 00:19:55.730
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

166
00:19:55.819 --> 00:20:00.650
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

167
00:20:02.609 --> 00:20:07.619
- These will protect you. They're magic!
- Acorns?

168
00:20:07.700 --> 00:20:11.710
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

169
00:20:14.789 --> 00:20:18.000
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

170
00:20:30.930 --> 00:20:35.400
- Are you scared. Dada?
- No!

171
00:20:35.480 --> 00:20:39.730
Even with fairies in the woods that'll
put you to sleep for a hundred years?

172
00:20:41.740 --> 00:20:43.859
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

173
00:20:43.950 --> 00:20:46.869
- Dragons?
- Trolls?

174
00:20:46.950 --> 00:20:50.369
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

175
00:20:50.450 --> 00:20:54.079
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

176
00:20:54.119 --> 00:20:57.289
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

177
00:20:57.339 --> 00:20:58.920
Me too. Me too. Dada.

178
00:21:00.509 --> 00:21:05.839
What a lucky father I am. I wish
I could take you bobbins with me.

179
00:21:08.930 --> 00:21:11.470
Good-bye. Dada.

180
00:21:13.519 --> 00:21:17.519
Go play!
Go on.

181
00:21:21.480 --> 00:21:25.029
We've never been apart.

182
00:21:26.069 --> 00:21:29.410
I miss you already.

183
00:21:30.740 --> 00:21:34.160
Don't worry. Kiaya.
I'll be fine.

184
00:21:34.250 --> 00:21:36.170
I'll be back
before you know it.

185
00:21:38.420 --> 00:21:41.170
Well. remember
to keep her warm.

186
00:21:43.210 --> 00:21:45.930
And... here.

187
00:21:48.049 --> 00:21:50.849
This will bring you luck.

188
00:22:04.029 --> 00:22:06.359
Good brave people!

189
00:22:08.200 --> 00:22:10.950
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

190
00:22:11.029 --> 00:22:15.750
Give the baby to the first
Daikini you see. then hurry home.

191
00:22:19.250 --> 00:22:22.839
Tuatha...
lokwathrak... tuatha!

192
00:22:22.920 --> 00:22:26.470
Going the direction the bird is flying!

193
00:22:26.549 --> 00:22:30.470
- Ooh.

194
00:22:30.549 --> 00:22:33.390
It's going back to the village!

195
00:22:35.230 --> 00:22:37.190
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

196
00:22:37.269 --> 00:22:39.519
Move out!

197
00:23:03.460 --> 00:23:06.920
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

198
00:23:07.009 --> 00:23:11.049
- We have to stop.
- Stop? Why?

199
00:23:11.089 --> 00:23:13.599
- The baby's sick.

200
00:23:17.559 --> 00:23:22.150
She's not sick!
Let me see.

201
00:23:22.230 --> 00:23:25.440
Uhaghh!
Take her! Take her!

202
00:23:28.029 --> 00:23:31.109
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

203
00:23:33.450 --> 00:23:35.119
Clean me up.

204
00:23:38.789 --> 00:23:42.000
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

205
00:23:42.079 --> 00:23:46.000
-Sorsha. you're useless!
-I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

206
00:23:46.049 --> 00:23:48.259
I'll find where
she hid the baby.

207
00:23:50.220 --> 00:23:52.470
Ah. General Kael. at last.

208
00:23:52.549 --> 00:23:57.269
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

209
00:23:57.349 --> 00:24:01.059
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

210
00:24:01.140 --> 00:24:06.609
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

211
00:24:06.690 --> 00:24:08.650
that continues
somehow to elude her.

212
00:24:10.569 --> 00:24:12.529
The baby of the prophecy?

213
00:24:12.609 --> 00:24:16.029
- The one that would destroy you?
- I need that baby alive.

214
00:24:16.119 --> 00:24:18.579
I must perform
the ritual that will...

215
00:24:18.660 --> 00:24:22.000
exile the child's spirit
into oblivion.

216
00:24:22.079 --> 00:24:24.829
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

217
00:24:24.880 --> 00:24:26.960
You'll do as I say. child.

218
00:24:33.390 --> 00:24:35.549
I read the signs.

219
00:24:35.640 --> 00:24:38.809
One day. I fear. your daughter
will betray you.

220
00:24:38.890 --> 00:24:43.059
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

221
00:24:58.789 --> 00:25:01.329
- Move!

222
00:25:01.410 --> 00:25:03.369
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

223
00:25:07.670 --> 00:25:11.380
- Come on!

224
00:25:20.970 --> 00:25:23.890
The Nelwyns have got the baby.
We've searched the village.

225
00:25:23.980 --> 00:25:26.940
But a group of them
Is on the road somewhere.

226
00:25:27.019 --> 00:25:28.859
They couldn' t have gone far!

227
00:25:28.900 --> 00:25:31.900
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

228
00:25:39.279 --> 00:25:42.000
Come. We'll keep to the woods.

229
00:26:20.779 --> 00:26:24.950
That's it!
It's the crossroads!

230
00:26:41.390 --> 00:26:44.349
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

231
00:26:49.849 --> 00:26:52.359
- What was that?

232
00:26:53.690 --> 00:26:56.490
Get the spears!

233
00:27:12.920 --> 00:27:14.880
- Uhh. Uhh.

234
00:27:14.920 --> 00:27:18.799
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

235
00:27:18.880 --> 00:27:21.299
Do you understand?

236
00:27:21.390 --> 00:27:23.259
- Water.
- Yeah.

237
00:27:25.390 --> 00:27:27.390
Hurry up!

238
00:27:31.400 --> 00:27:34.319
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks.

239
00:27:34.400 --> 00:27:37.859
It's a Daikini.
We're in luck.

240
00:27:37.940 --> 00:27:40.359
We can't give her to him!

241
00:27:40.410 --> 00:27:44.369
- Somebody put him there for a reason.
- We've got to get rid of her.

242
00:27:44.450 --> 00:27:47.039
- Those soldiers are after us.
- Shhh.

243
00:27:47.119 --> 00:27:50.000
He's looking right at us.

244
00:27:53.920 --> 00:27:55.920
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

245
00:27:55.960 --> 00:27:58.839
I'm somebody.

246
00:27:58.920 --> 00:28:03.259
Let me out of here. I'll take care
of the baby.

247
00:28:05.099 --> 00:28:09.730
- I trust him completely.
- But he tried to strangle me.

248
00:28:09.769 --> 00:28:13.730
- I want to go home!
- No. Burglekutt!

249
00:28:13.809 --> 00:28:17.150
- We should wait!
- Are you challenging my authority?

250
00:28:17.230 --> 00:28:20.609
As far as this baby
is concerned... yes.

251
00:28:20.650 --> 00:28:23.700
Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.

252
00:28:23.779 --> 00:28:28.869
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

253
00:28:28.950 --> 00:28:31.160
That's a bad idea.
Very bad.

254
00:28:31.250 --> 00:28:34.670
- Dangerous out there.
- Get the gear. men.

255
00:28:34.750 --> 00:28:38.299
- vohnkar-
- It's not his decision!

256
00:28:38.380 --> 00:28:42.299
Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

257
00:28:42.380 --> 00:28:44.049
Don't let him
talk to you that way.

258
00:28:44.140 --> 00:28:46.220
Listen here. runt.

259
00:28:46.299 --> 00:28:50.269
While you're wasting time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.

260
00:28:50.349 --> 00:28:54.650
- Think about it!
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna-

261
00:28:54.730 --> 00:28:58.109
You're gonna what?

262
00:29:01.990 --> 00:29:04.569
Some day. Burglekutt.
Some day.

263
00:29:04.660 --> 00:29:06.660
Vohnkar. let's go!

264
00:29:10.329 --> 00:29:13.039
Meegosh. are you coming?

265
00:29:15.329 --> 00:29:18.920
- I'm staying.
- Come on. men.

266
00:29:19.000 --> 00:29:23.170
Burglekutt. Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

267
00:29:23.259 --> 00:29:25.930
just let me out of here.
Please!

268
00:29:26.009 --> 00:29:29.470
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear...
just for a minute.

269
00:29:29.509 --> 00:29:31.809
Get-
Well. at least get me some water!

270
00:29:31.849 --> 00:29:36.809
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two!

271
00:29:36.900 --> 00:29:41.690
- What'll we do now. Willow?

272
00:29:41.779 --> 00:29:44.400
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

273
00:29:44.490 --> 00:29:49.279
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry... peck.

274
00:29:49.369 --> 00:29:53.119
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

275
00:29:53.200 --> 00:29:56.960
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

276
00:29:58.380 --> 00:30:02.880
- I'll throw it. and turn you to stone.
- Whoo-

277
00:30:02.960 --> 00:30:04.920
I'm really scared.

278
00:30:04.970 --> 00:30:07.839
No. don't! Don't!

279
00:30:07.890 --> 00:30:10.720
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

280
00:30:10.809 --> 00:30:13.480
Oh. I wouldn't
want to waste it.

281
00:30:13.559 --> 00:30:16.809
Ha!
Peck. peck. peck. peck.

282
00:30:16.900 --> 00:30:19.440
peck. peck. peck.
peck. peck!

283
00:30:48.049 --> 00:30:50.930
- What was that?

284
00:30:54.309 --> 00:30:58.019
Mornin'. boys.

285
00:30:58.099 --> 00:31:02.230
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

286
00:31:02.269 --> 00:31:05.650
I don't think I introduced
myself yesterday.

287
00:31:05.740 --> 00:31:09.200
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh-

288
00:31:09.279 --> 00:31:12.240
No. Meegosh.
Don't go near him.

289
00:31:12.279 --> 00:31:15.750
- He's dangerous.
- I am not.

290
00:31:15.789 --> 00:31:17.960
Good.

291
00:31:22.710 --> 00:31:25.009
Stop! Wait!

292
00:31:26.759 --> 00:31:29.509
- Whoa!

293
00:31:34.970 --> 00:31:39.480
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

294
00:31:39.559 --> 00:31:42.059
I suppose you're a warrior.

295
00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:44.650
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

296
00:31:44.730 --> 00:31:47.569
Humph.

297
00:31:47.650 --> 00:31:51.410
Say. uh- Could I have
some of that water?

298
00:32:01.119 --> 00:32:05.880
I don't know why I try.

299
00:32:10.680 --> 00:32:13.930
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares.

300
00:32:14.009 --> 00:32:15.930
- Here.
- Thanks. friend. Oh!

301
00:32:16.009 --> 00:32:18.390
- What's that?

302
00:32:18.480 --> 00:32:22.440
I'd say
two or three hundred horses.

303
00:32:22.519 --> 00:32:26.480
five or six wagons...
and about a thousand fools.

304
00:32:29.190 --> 00:32:32.990
- Thank you. Ohh-
- Come on. Meegosh.

305
00:32:37.329 --> 00:32:41.039
It's gonna be
all right. little bobbin.

306
00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:50.920
- Everything's gonna be all right.

307
00:32:54.259 --> 00:32:57.349
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

308
00:32:59.309 --> 00:33:01.690
Uh. pardon me.

309
00:33:01.730 --> 00:33:03.849
Uh-

310
00:33:09.480 --> 00:33:14.700
Excuse me. sir. We found one
of your babies in our village.

311
00:33:14.779 --> 00:33:17.700
Will you please
take care of her?

312
00:33:17.779 --> 00:33:22.210
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

313
00:33:23.619 --> 00:33:26.789
They thought you were
a woman. Airk.

314
00:33:26.880 --> 00:33:29.250
Well-

315
00:33:29.339 --> 00:33:33.880
-Madmartigan. what did you do this time?
-Nothing you wouldn't have done.

316
00:33:33.970 --> 00:33:36.339
I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

317
00:33:36.430 --> 00:33:38.259
At least I'm not
down there herding sheep.

318
00:33:38.349 --> 00:33:39.849
What are you doing this far north?

319
00:33:39.930 --> 00:33:41.930
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

320
00:33:42.930 --> 00:33:44.269
The castle?

321
00:33:44.309 --> 00:33:46.769
Bavmorda's troops are
crushing everything in sight.

322
00:33:46.859 --> 00:33:48.769
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

323
00:33:48.859 --> 00:33:51.109
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

324
00:33:51.230 --> 00:33:55.529
Madmartigan-
I still serve Galladoorn.

325
00:33:55.609 --> 00:33:57.569
You serve no one.

326
00:33:57.660 --> 00:33:59.910
Remember?

327
00:33:59.990 --> 00:34:03.200
Sit in your coffin and rot.

328
00:34:03.289 --> 00:34:06.329
- Hyah!
- Wait. Airk. You need me!

329
00:34:06.420 --> 00:34:08.840
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

330
00:34:08.920 --> 00:34:11.550
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...

331
00:34:11.630 --> 00:34:13.719
and stick it
on a pig pole!

332
00:34:31.230 --> 00:34:35.949
- I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

333
00:34:39.949 --> 00:34:43.750
We're running out of food.

334
00:34:43.829 --> 00:34:47.460
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

335
00:34:47.500 --> 00:34:50.500
You know why?
Nobody cares.

336
00:34:53.380 --> 00:34:56.929
Except me.

337
00:34:57.010 --> 00:35:01.219
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

338
00:35:01.300 --> 00:35:05.269
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

339
00:35:05.349 --> 00:35:08.309
I believe he would. Willow.

340
00:35:08.400 --> 00:35:10.940
He doesn't know
anything about babies.

341
00:35:11.019 --> 00:35:16.239
Right. But I know
a lot of women who do.

342
00:35:16.320 --> 00:35:19.239
If I had somebody in my life.

343
00:35:19.320 --> 00:35:22.909
a little daughter. perhaps.

344
00:35:22.989 --> 00:35:26.250
I might have a reason
to go on living.

345
00:35:29.500 --> 00:35:32.289
You can't leave me
in here to die.

346
00:35:32.380 --> 00:35:35.420
Not when all I want
to do is protect her.

347
00:35:48.730 --> 00:35:52.650
I feel better!

348
00:35:52.730 --> 00:35:56.440
-You've done the right thing! -Okay. All right. All right.

349
00:35:56.530 --> 00:36:00.989
- You gotta promise to feed her.
- Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

350
00:36:01.070 --> 00:36:06.079
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

351
00:36:06.159 --> 00:36:08.199
- Hee. hee. hee!

352
00:36:08.289 --> 00:36:13.170
- Wheee!

353
00:36:13.250 --> 00:36:16.500
She likes me.

354
00:36:18.590 --> 00:36:20.969
Here are her changing rags.

355
00:36:21.050 --> 00:36:23.260
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

356
00:36:23.300 --> 00:36:27.599
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

357
00:36:29.309 --> 00:36:32.849
- You wory too much. peck.

358
00:36:32.940 --> 00:36:36.860
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

359
00:36:36.940 --> 00:36:42.699
Now listen. boys- Willow.
You've done the right thing.

360
00:36:42.780 --> 00:36:46.159
And I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

361
00:36:52.670 --> 00:36:56.920
- Good-bye. little one.

362
00:37:05.639 --> 00:37:07.889
Please. take good care of her.

363
00:37:09.679 --> 00:37:12.519
I give you my word of honor!

364
00:37:19.190 --> 00:37:23.110
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

365
00:37:23.150 --> 00:37:27.409
If we hurry. we can be home by
tomorrow morning. We'll be heroes.

366
00:37:27.489 --> 00:37:31.000
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

367
00:37:31.079 --> 00:37:33.329
"Look. there's
Willow and Meegosh.

368
00:37:33.420 --> 00:37:35.630
The heroes have come home."

369
00:37:35.710 --> 00:37:38.800
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

370
00:37:38.880 --> 00:37:43.130
- Yeah. Medals.

371
00:37:43.170 --> 00:37:46.929
Meegosh-

372
00:37:48.809 --> 00:37:52.929
- Did we do the right thing?
- Absolutely.

373
00:37:53.019 --> 00:37:57.309
- There's nothing to wory about.

374
00:38:00.320 --> 00:38:02.610
Hyah! Ha!

375
00:38:02.690 --> 00:38:07.909
I stole the baby! I stole the baby!

376
00:38:07.989 --> 00:38:11.750
- Hyah!
- That's my baby!

377
00:38:11.829 --> 00:38:13.789
- Stop! Wait! Come back!

378
00:38:13.869 --> 00:38:17.039
Left. you stupid bird.
Left! Ha ha!

379
00:38:19.840 --> 00:38:23.090
- Ah!
- Ow!

380
00:38:23.170 --> 00:38:26.840
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

381
00:38:26.929 --> 00:38:30.260
- Come on. Meegosh!
- Ow!

382
00:38:31.260 --> 00:38:35.019
- Uhh-uh-huh-uh.
- Uhh. Oww!

383
00:38:36.309 --> 00:38:38.360
We'll outrun 'em!

384
00:38:43.110 --> 00:38:47.199
-Hey. ugly. wake up!-

385
00:38:47.280 --> 00:38:49.739
Huh?

386
00:38:49.780 --> 00:38:54.909
- Stand your ground. He's our prisoner.

387
00:38:54.949 --> 00:38:57.750
Meegosh.
where's the baby?

388
00:38:57.789 --> 00:38:59.750
Bring the Nelwyns tome.

389
00:38:59.789 --> 00:39:01.210
All right. you heard her!

390
00:39:01.289 --> 00:39:05.090
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

391
00:39:05.130 --> 00:39:07.510
You are mine to toy with.

392
00:39:07.590 --> 00:39:11.099
Forward!

393
00:39:11.179 --> 00:39:14.969
- Gimme the rope.

394
00:39:15.059 --> 00:39:19.059
Where-
Where...

395
00:39:19.150 --> 00:39:21.440
did you get that baby?

396
00:39:21.480 --> 00:39:26.239
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

397
00:39:26.400 --> 00:39:29.570
Franjean. release the Nelwyns.

398
00:39:29.610 --> 00:39:33.909
-And stop pestering them.
- Uh-oh.

399
00:39:33.989 --> 00:39:36.079
Ahh-

400
00:39:38.329 --> 00:39:40.289
- Yaah!

401
00:39:44.550 --> 00:39:47.800
- You!

402
00:39:47.840 --> 00:39:52.929
Welcome to my kingdom.

403
00:39:59.099 --> 00:40:03.610
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

404
00:40:03.690 --> 00:40:06.940
Blora Danan told me.

405
00:40:06.989 --> 00:40:10.320
Blora?
Blora. Willow is here.

406
00:40:13.119 --> 00:40:18.659
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

407
00:40:18.750 --> 00:40:24.090
My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.

408
00:40:24.170 --> 00:40:29.090
Blora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

409
00:40:29.170 --> 00:40:33.929
- Me?
- Yes. She likes you.

410
00:40:35.349 --> 00:40:40.309
And Elora Danan knows you
have the courage to help us.

411
00:40:40.389 --> 00:40:43.980
Take my wand
to the sorceress. Find Raziel.

412
00:40:44.059 --> 00:40:48.320
She will guide you and Blora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen.

413
00:40:48.360 --> 00:40:51.489
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

414
00:40:51.530 --> 00:40:55.329
You need a warrior for
a job like this. I'm a nobody.

415
00:40:55.489 --> 00:40:58.750
Blora. you don't want me.

416
00:40:58.829 --> 00:41:02.539
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

417
00:41:05.500 --> 00:41:08.130
Hello?

418
00:41:15.469 --> 00:41:18.889
Blora Danan must survive!

419
00:41:18.929 --> 00:41:23.809
She must fulfill her destiny and bring
about the downfall of Queen Bavmorda.

420
00:41:23.849 --> 00:41:26.730
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

421
00:41:26.769 --> 00:41:31.150
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...

422
00:41:31.190 --> 00:41:35.780
of your village.
your children- everyone.

423
00:41:40.449 --> 00:41:43.960
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

424
00:41:44.039 --> 00:41:49.250
The choice is yours.

425
00:42:11.820 --> 00:42:16.070
- Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.
- Huh?

426
00:42:16.110 --> 00:42:20.369
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

427
00:42:22.949 --> 00:42:26.500
Listen. Meegosh.
Tell Kiaya I love her.

428
00:42:26.579 --> 00:42:31.130
- And I think of her every day.
- Willow-

429
00:42:31.210 --> 00:42:34.670
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

430
00:42:34.760 --> 00:42:37.389
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

431
00:42:37.469 --> 00:42:40.389
I hope so.

432
00:42:40.469 --> 00:42:44.059
Listen. be careful.

433
00:42:50.150 --> 00:42:54.690
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

434
00:42:54.780 --> 00:42:58.239
-I am the leader!
- How long will it take to find Raziel?

435
00:42:58.320 --> 00:43:02.789
Um. not long. She's been exiled
to an island just over those hills.

436
00:43:02.869 --> 00:43:05.960
- She's what?
- Exiled...

437
00:43:06.039 --> 00:43:09.880
by the evil Queen Bavmorda.

438
00:43:09.960 --> 00:43:12.590
Rool. You fool. He does
not need to know everything.

439
00:43:12.670 --> 00:43:15.260
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

440
00:43:15.340 --> 00:43:17.630
- You mentioned the island. the queen.
- Wait a minute.

441
00:43:17.679 --> 00:43:20.349
So?

442
00:43:20.429 --> 00:43:23.219
What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?

443
00:43:23.309 --> 00:43:25.929
Don't play with that wand.

444
00:43:25.980 --> 00:43:28.559
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

445
00:43:28.650 --> 00:43:31.110
Only a great sorcerer can use it.

446
00:43:31.190 --> 00:43:33.940
-Not a stupid peck like you.

447
00:43:33.980 --> 00:43:37.150
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

448
00:43:37.239 --> 00:43:39.530
- All right. then this way.
- Bah. nope.

449
00:43:39.610 --> 00:43:42.119
- This way.
- This way?

450
00:43:42.199 --> 00:43:45.949
- That's what I said.
- This way.

451
00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:49.460
- You know where you're going?
- Of course.

452
00:43:49.539 --> 00:43:52.250
With us as your guides
no harm with befall you.

453
00:44:02.679 --> 00:44:06.849
- Take it up!

454
00:44:08.349 --> 00:44:12.610
- We are not going in there!
- But Blora needs fresh milk.

455
00:44:12.690 --> 00:44:17.530
- And we are drenched.
- You are not in command. shorty. I am!

456
00:44:17.610 --> 00:44:21.199
- You hear me?
- Whoa!

457
00:44:58.940 --> 00:45:01.400
- Excuse me? Excuse me.

458
00:45:01.449 --> 00:45:04.409
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

459
00:45:04.489 --> 00:45:06.369
Get out of here. peck!

460
00:45:06.449 --> 00:45:08.789
Get outta here
or we'll cook ya!

461
00:45:22.179 --> 00:45:26.099
Ooh. look at her!

462
00:45:26.139 --> 00:45:28.429
I could use
a love potion on her!

463
00:45:28.469 --> 00:45:32.309
Franjean! Hey! Give me that
dust of broken heart.

464
00:45:32.389 --> 00:45:34.099
- Come on! Give it to me!
- Let go of me!

465
00:45:34.190 --> 00:45:37.570
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

466
00:45:41.739 --> 00:45:43.739
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

467
00:45:50.699 --> 00:45:54.460
Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

468
00:45:56.750 --> 00:46:01.880
You are so beautiful!

469
00:46:01.969 --> 00:46:05.590
- Your eyes! Your whiskers!

470
00:46:05.679 --> 00:46:08.300
- I have to kiss you!
-Rool!

471
00:46:08.389 --> 00:46:10.139
That dust of broken heart!

472
00:46:24.989 --> 00:46:27.199
Beer!

473
00:46:30.329 --> 00:46:32.449
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

474
00:46:37.039 --> 00:46:39.039
Hurry! Hurry!

475
00:46:39.130 --> 00:46:41.000
My husband's coming!

476
00:46:41.090 --> 00:46:43.130
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

477
00:46:43.210 --> 00:46:45.840
- How do I look?
- Not you!

478
00:46:47.050 --> 00:46:48.969
Where the hell
did you come from?

479
00:46:49.050 --> 00:46:51.309
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

480
00:46:51.349 --> 00:46:55.190
Don't I know you?
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.

481
00:46:55.269 --> 00:46:57.480
- While you were taking a pee-pee!
- Cover your face!

482
00:46:57.559 --> 00:47:01.190
- You are crawling with Brownies.
- I hate Brownies!

483
00:47:01.230 --> 00:47:04.070
Whoa!

484
00:47:04.150 --> 00:47:06.739
- Where is he? Where?
- Hello. dear.

485
00:47:06.820 --> 00:47:09.199
There's nobody here but
me and. uh. my. uh-

486
00:47:09.239 --> 00:47:11.659
- I'll kill him!
- ...my cousin. Hilda.

487
00:47:11.739 --> 00:47:14.000
- Hilda?
- Hilda.

488
00:47:14.039 --> 00:47:16.159
- Oh. Hilda!
- This is my husband. Llug.

489
00:47:16.250 --> 00:47:19.000
- Mmm... Big husband.
- Yes.

490
00:47:19.079 --> 00:47:20.920
- How do you do?

491
00:47:21.000 --> 00:47:23.380
Hilda! Ooh.

492
00:47:23.420 --> 00:47:25.550
Come on. girly.
Don't be shy.

493
00:47:25.630 --> 00:47:28.260
- Hey! Give her back!

494
00:47:28.340 --> 00:47:30.719
- Pecks make terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

495
00:47:30.800 --> 00:47:33.719
- They get too excited.

496
00:47:33.769 --> 00:47:36.389
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

497
00:47:36.480 --> 00:47:38.519
- Huh?
- Hey. hey. hey. hey!

498
00:47:38.599 --> 00:47:43.230
- Stop. please. Ooh.

499
00:47:43.320 --> 00:47:45.190
Come on.
Fight like a man!

500
00:47:45.239 --> 00:47:48.280
- Want to breed?

501
00:47:48.360 --> 00:47:51.369
Tempting. but no.

502
00:47:54.289 --> 00:47:56.250
Thank you.
Time to leave.

503
00:47:56.289 --> 00:47:58.250
- Bye. Hilda!
- Take them out.

504
00:47:58.289 --> 00:48:01.460
- Hey! Come along!

505
00:48:01.539 --> 00:48:04.130
- Careful. you lout!
- Move along!

506
00:48:04.210 --> 00:48:06.920
Gather pall these babies.

507
00:48:07.010 --> 00:48:09.260
That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

508
00:48:13.010 --> 00:48:15.139
That's not the one.

509
00:48:18.849 --> 00:48:21.599
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

510
00:48:21.690 --> 00:48:24.269
- Yes. Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

511
00:48:24.360 --> 00:48:25.940
No! Don't let her!

512
00:48:26.030 --> 00:48:27.489
Aah!

513
00:48:27.570 --> 00:48:30.449
I gave you an order. woman!

514
00:48:39.789 --> 00:48:43.250
You-
You're... beautiful.

515
00:48:43.340 --> 00:48:46.670
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

516
00:48:49.260 --> 00:48:51.760
You're no woman!

517
00:48:51.840 --> 00:48:53.679
- Now. honey. take it easy.
- Not a woman?

518
00:48:53.760 --> 00:48:56.639
- Gentlemen.
- Not a woman?

519
00:48:56.679 --> 00:48:59.480
- Meet Llug.

520
00:49:00.769 --> 00:49:02.809
- After them!
- Out of the way!

521
00:49:09.110 --> 00:49:10.360
- To the horses!

522
00:49:10.360 --> 00:49:11.449
- To the horses!

523
00:49:13.989 --> 00:49:16.449
Hey! What are you doing?

524
00:49:20.829 --> 00:49:22.750
- Hyah!

525
00:49:22.829 --> 00:49:26.750
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

526
00:49:30.219 --> 00:49:35.099
- He's not a woman!
- To your horses! Hyah! Hyah!

527
00:49:35.179 --> 00:49:37.559
Don't let them get away!

528
00:49:39.219 --> 00:49:42.639
- Madmartigan. stop!
- What?

529
00:49:54.449 --> 00:49:56.489
Hyah!

530
00:50:01.619 --> 00:50:04.119
Madmartigan.
I'm warning you-

531
00:50:06.170 --> 00:50:09.840
- Ow!
- Prepare to die!

532
00:50:33.239 --> 00:50:35.570
Madmartigan!
Stop!

533
00:51:05.639 --> 00:51:07.690
Franjean. help me!

534
00:51:12.320 --> 00:51:14.239
- Rool!
- Help!

535
00:51:14.320 --> 00:51:17.360
Rool! Rool.

536
00:51:18.530 --> 00:51:22.329
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

537
00:51:27.710 --> 00:51:29.960
- Come on. I am.
- Pull me in.

538
00:51:30.039 --> 00:51:32.500
Yeah. pull!

539
00:51:50.690 --> 00:51:52.690
You can't have her!

540
00:51:58.610 --> 00:52:00.320
Whoa!

541
00:52:05.039 --> 00:52:08.619
- Rool. this isn't funny!

542
00:52:08.710 --> 00:52:10.630
Help me cut the rope!

543
00:52:23.809 --> 00:52:26.559
Who-oa!

544
00:52:48.079 --> 00:52:50.670
Willow. stay down!

545
00:52:54.380 --> 00:52:56.420
Whoa!

546
00:52:56.460 --> 00:52:58.719
Whoa!

547
00:52:58.800 --> 00:53:00.719
Gone crazy?

548
00:53:00.800 --> 00:53:02.929
You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

549
00:53:03.010 --> 00:53:05.429
- We're getting off!
- Hyah!

550
00:53:05.469 --> 00:53:08.099
Oh! Hold on! Hyah!

551
00:53:30.909 --> 00:53:33.420
Whoa! Whoa!

552
00:53:36.590 --> 00:53:38.920
- Oh. Rool.

553
00:53:39.010 --> 00:53:42.679
Now we stop. peck.

554
00:53:42.760 --> 00:53:48.059
Stupid Daikini.
Ask him to stop the wagon.

555
00:53:48.099 --> 00:53:52.309
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

556
00:53:53.809 --> 00:53:56.309
I just saved that infant's life!

557
00:53:57.769 --> 00:54:00.110
Hah! Hah!

558
00:54:00.190 --> 00:54:02.150
Gather your wits. Come on.

559
00:54:02.199 --> 00:54:05.239
- Don't wory about me.
-Come on!

560
00:54:06.320 --> 00:54:08.489
- Get down!

561
00:54:08.579 --> 00:54:10.949
Uh. where am I?
Oh!

562
00:54:12.869 --> 00:54:14.960
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

563
00:54:31.469 --> 00:54:34.059
-Ah. Franjean!
- You better clear out. Willow.

564
00:54:34.139 --> 00:54:35.599
Before those troops come back.

565
00:54:35.650 --> 00:54:39.110
- Ah. my head!
- We don't need him. Blora.

566
00:54:47.530 --> 00:54:49.619
Madmartigan. wait!

567
00:54:49.659 --> 00:54:53.000
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

568
00:54:53.079 --> 00:54:55.039
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

569
00:54:55.119 --> 00:54:58.340
My help? What do you need my help for?

570
00:54:58.420 --> 00:55:00.590
You're a sorcerer!

571
00:55:00.670 --> 00:55:03.880
You're a great warrior.
and a swordsman.

572
00:55:03.969 --> 00:55:06.840
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

573
00:55:06.929 --> 00:55:10.179
Are you tying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

574
00:55:13.429 --> 00:55:18.360
- Hurry! Big dogs!

575
00:55:18.440 --> 00:55:22.690
Look. I'm sorry
I got angry.

576
00:55:22.730 --> 00:55:24.690
We wouldn't have
escaped without you.

577
00:55:38.880 --> 00:55:41.710
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

578
00:55:43.210 --> 00:55:46.840
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

579
00:55:47.880 --> 00:55:51.050
That way.

580
00:55:51.099 --> 00:55:54.719
You are drunk. and when you
are drunk you forget that...

581
00:55:54.809 --> 00:55:56.730
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

582
00:55:56.809 --> 00:55:59.019
Fine.
Then which way do we go?

583
00:55:59.099 --> 00:56:01.110
That way!

584
00:56:04.150 --> 00:56:08.699
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

585
00:56:08.739 --> 00:56:11.739
All right. all right. You can
follow me as far as the lake.

586
00:56:11.829 --> 00:56:14.039
But that's it!

587
00:56:14.079 --> 00:56:17.869
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

588
00:56:17.909 --> 00:56:23.090
Good. Mumbo-Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go and get me some eggs or something.

589
00:56:23.170 --> 00:56:25.800
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

590
00:56:32.510 --> 00:56:37.179
Kael. have you found the child?

591
00:56:37.269 --> 00:56:39.019
The search goes on. my queen.

592
00:56:40.099 --> 00:56:42.110
Why. with my powers.

593
00:56:42.190 --> 00:56:45.400
with the strength
of my great army.

594
00:56:45.480 --> 00:56:48.900
can you not find
one little child?

595
00:56:48.949 --> 00:56:51.280
We look even now.
It won't be long.

596
00:56:51.360 --> 00:56:54.739
Find the child.
Find the child!

597
00:56:54.780 --> 00:56:57.409
Time is running out.

598
00:57:01.579 --> 00:57:06.000
- Good night.

599
00:57:06.050 --> 00:57:09.380
She is kinda cute.

600
00:57:09.469 --> 00:57:11.219
When she's quiet.

601
00:57:12.639 --> 00:57:14.550
She's really a princess.

602
00:57:14.639 --> 00:57:18.639
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

603
00:57:18.730 --> 00:57:20.639
And I'm the king of Cashmere.

604
00:57:20.730 --> 00:57:24.519
Go to sleep. Willow.

605
00:57:24.610 --> 00:57:27.110
Good night. Madmartigan.

606
00:57:27.150 --> 00:57:30.150
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

607
00:57:30.199 --> 00:57:33.530
Uh- Uh! Oh!
Rats! Ra-

608
00:57:33.619 --> 00:57:36.530
Oh. Rool. you had
that stupid rat dream!

609
00:57:47.340 --> 00:57:50.050
Tuatha...

610
00:57:50.130 --> 00:57:52.300
Lawkathok...

611
00:57:52.380 --> 00:57:54.300
- Tuatha!

612
00:57:54.340 --> 00:57:57.099
Huh?
Willow?

613
00:57:58.179 --> 00:58:00.309
Willow?

614
00:58:02.059 --> 00:58:04.519
Oh. There you are.

615
00:58:04.599 --> 00:58:06.559
Madmartigan!

616
00:58:06.650 --> 00:58:09.980
'Night. Willow.

617
00:58:22.079 --> 00:58:24.079
This way! This way!

618
00:58:35.889 --> 00:58:37.849
What are you doing?

619
00:58:37.889 --> 00:58:40.269
I found some black root.
She loves it!

620
00:58:40.349 --> 00:58:43.269
Black root? I am
the father of two children.

621
00:58:43.349 --> 00:58:45.349
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

622
00:58:45.519 --> 00:58:48.570
Well. my mother
raised us on black root.

623
00:58:48.650 --> 00:58:51.190
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

624
00:58:51.280 --> 00:58:54.030
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

625
00:58:54.401 --> 00:58:57.361
She's Blora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

626
00:58:57.401 --> 00:58:59.740
And the last thing she's gonna
want is a hairy chest!

627
00:59:03.910 --> 00:59:05.950
Did you see what he did?

628
00:59:06.040 --> 00:59:09.290
He stole our black root. I'll get
some more. don't wory about it.

629
00:59:14.131 --> 00:59:17.470
- There it is! The island!

630
00:59:19.680 --> 00:59:21.591
We made it.

631
00:59:21.680 --> 00:59:26.220
We have led you to
the island of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

632
00:59:26.310 --> 00:59:30.560
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat.

633
00:59:48.620 --> 00:59:50.620
Well. looks like
I got you here.

634
00:59:50.710 --> 00:59:53.170
You!
What did you do?

635
00:59:53.250 --> 00:59:56.250
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs! Huh?

636
00:59:56.341 --> 00:59:58.300
I found a boat.
We're all set.

637
00:59:58.381 --> 01:00:02.300
Good. Take these two lizards
out and drown them.

638
01:00:02.390 --> 01:00:05.720
- Who are you calling lizards?
- Heh? Heh?

639
01:00:07.810 --> 01:00:10.480
Your mother was lizard!

640
01:00:13.480 --> 01:00:15.980
- Good-bye. Sticks.

641
01:00:18.651 --> 01:00:21.570
If you really are a princess.

642
01:00:21.651 --> 01:00:24.620
take care of him.

643
01:00:30.960 --> 01:00:34.250
- Madmartigan!
- What?

644
01:00:34.330 --> 01:00:36.210
Thanks.

645
01:00:45.720 --> 01:00:48.260
Hey! Aah!

646
01:00:48.310 --> 01:00:51.680
-Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turnaround!

647
01:00:52.850 --> 01:00:55.861
- It's all right. Blora.

648
01:00:55.940 --> 01:00:58.361
- Go to sleep.

649
01:00:58.440 --> 01:01:00.780
- Nobody'll find you here.

650
01:01:00.861 --> 01:01:02.450
I'll be back with
Fin Raziel very soon.

651
01:01:02.490 --> 01:01:05.820
We will guard her
with our meager lives.

